Putting this all together, it seems like there's an attempt to create scheduled tasks that execute calc.exe at system startup or logon. This could be part of a persistence mechanism used by malware to ensure it runs every time the user logs in or the system starts up.

The repeated Registry modifications and process creations also add to the suspicion. While individual events might not be alarming, the combination points towards potential malicious activity aimed at establishing persistence on the system.
